\begin_layout Subsection
Segment end detector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Segment end detector processes request to end currend Bit time segment as
 is shown in Table TODO.
 Segment end detector captures these requests and processes them when Time
 Quanta has elapsed.
 If request arrives in the same clock cycle as Time Quanta has elapsed,
 it is processed immediately.
 Based on these requests, Segment End Detector detects end of segment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Bit rate switch
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since both Bit time counters (Nominal and Data) are running in bits where
 Bit-rate is switched, length of TSEG2 of these bits is measured by both
 counters and both resynchronisation modules can signal request to end current
 segment.
 Segment end detector only considers requests from the Resynchronisation
 module of which is given by actual Sample control as given by Protocol
 Control FSM.
 This situation is shown in Figure TODO.
 Note that since Protocol control provides Sample control already in Process
 pipeline stage (due to speculative forwarding), there might occur negative
 re-synchronisation which shortens duration of TSEG2 after BRS to just one
 clock cycle.
 In this case following TX Trigger is throttled as mentioned in TODO.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
